00:52:29,920 --> 00:52:34,350
but we're filming a variety show about Manitos...

1719
00:52:33,140 --> 00:52:37,420
[Summary: We hope to prepare a gift
for kids who love badminton]

1720
00:52:37,370 --> 00:52:41,030
We just arrived in the country today.

1721
00:52:38,140 --> 00:52:42,900
[An Seyoung, who is traveling
for the World Tour Finals tournament]

1722
00:52:41,240 --> 00:52:43,620
An Seyoung is still at the airport check-in.

1723
00:52:43,580 --> 00:52:47,060
[An Seyoung's manager:
It depends on the situation...]

1724
00:52:43,760 --> 00:52:46,900
OK.

1725
00:52:47,050 --> 00:52:49,730
It's for a good cause.

1726
00:52:49,820 --> 00:52:54,740
[Jennie: We're preparing heartwarming
end-of-year gifts for elementary school kids.]

1727
00:52:54,710 --> 00:52:58,370
If it's not too much trouble,
I hope you can convey it to her.

1728
00:52:55,300 --> 00:53:02,100
[Please]

1729
00:52:58,490 --> 00:52:59,650
-If it's possible. -Sure.

1730
00:52:59,650 --> 00:53:02,160
Please call us anytime. Thank you.

1731
00:53:02,100 --> 00:53:06,220
[An Seyoung's manager: I'll try to
convey it to her and ask her by tonight.]

1732
00:53:02,290 --> 00:53:03,300
OK.

1733
00:53:06,620 --> 00:53:09,820
[Making a delicate request
despite her tight schedule]

1734
00:53:07,240 --> 00:53:08,940
-Thank you. -Thank you.

1735
00:53:09,260 --> 00:53:11,550
-No problem. -Goodbye.

1736
00:53:10,540 --> 00:53:12,340
[Bowing 90 degrees to the phone out of gratitude]

1737
00:53:12,820 --> 00:53:16,340
[We did it. We did it!]

1738
00:53:14,410 --> 00:53:15,810
A cause for celebration.

1739
00:53:19,540 --> 00:53:23,340
[Each focused on packaging their own gifts]

1740
00:53:31,340 --> 00:53:34,550
[Sooji, what did you write in the letters?]

1741
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:38,100
Do you want to check out a few of my letters?

1742
00:53:44,580 --> 00:53:49,180
[Reading the letters slowly]

1743
00:53:50,220 --> 00:53:55,340
[Sooji was referring to something
while writing the letters]

1744
00:53:56,380 --> 00:54:01,860
[She kept writing in the car]

1745
00:54:02,740 --> 00:54:06,860
[She noted down notable features of every kid]

1746
00:54:07,340 --> 00:54:11,720
[Lee Sooji: Tiago's unfamiliar with Korean,
so I wrote bigger for his letter.]

1747
00:54:11,720 --> 00:54:15,100
[Lee Sooji: But he wants to be good at Korean.]

1748
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:16,940
So I wrote it big so that he can understand it.

1749
00:54:17,180 --> 00:54:22,700
[Customizing their letters
based on their characteristics]

1750
00:54:23,380 --> 00:54:29,860
[Even giving up her break to convey her sincerity]

1751
00:54:30,530 --> 00:54:32,130
Sooji.

1752
00:54:30,860 --> 00:54:35,780
[Totally touched]

1753
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:35,180
I can't hold a candle to you.

1754
00:54:35,380 --> 00:54:36,220
It's OK.

1755
00:54:36,500 --> 00:54:39,380
[Lee Sooji: Your design and art
are already heartwarming.]

1756
00:54:39,960 --> 00:54:41,170
But see.

1757
00:54:41,340 --> 00:54:44,780
["Please let me win the lottery.
I want to make a lot of money."]

1758
00:54:44,140 --> 00:54:46,300
Why don't you write him a few numbers?

1759
00:54:46,400 --> 00:54:49,170
And specify, "Please convey it to your father."

1760
00:54:49,660 --> 00:54:50,920
[What grade and class is he in?]

1761
00:54:50,920 --> 00:54:52,180
[Class 1 of the 5th grade.]

1762
00:54:52,940 --> 00:54:56,380
[Possessed by General Baekdu]

1763
00:54:54,240 --> 00:54:56,460
No. 1 and No. 5.

1764
00:54:56,820 --> 00:54:59,700
[And his student number in class.]

1765
00:55:00,100 --> 00:55:03,860
[How can I write numbers
in a letter to convey sincerity?]

1766
00:55:00,320 --> 00:55:03,420
I can't write lottery numbers in here, can I?

1767
00:55:04,420 --> 00:55:06,180
[Lee Sooji: Fine, then let's each say a number.]

1768
00:55:06,420 --> 00:55:07,700
[No. 4!]

1769
00:55:07,650 --> 00:55:08,100
4.

1770
00:55:08,100 --> 00:55:11,300
[I'm really writing them down.]

1771
00:55:09,520 --> 00:55:10,950
Write it for real.

1772
00:55:11,530 --> 00:55:13,040
-9. -9.

1773
00:55:13,150 --> 00:55:14,310
13.

1774
00:55:14,590 --> 00:55:15,590
-They have to be bigger. -17.

1775
00:55:15,590 --> 00:55:16,650
17?

1776
00:55:17,260 --> 00:55:18,340
[How about you, Jennie?]

1777
00:55:18,500 --> 00:55:20,860
[Can't help but think carefully]

1778
00:55:20,860 --> 00:55:23,420
[Why am I nervous about this?]

1779
00:55:24,180 --> 00:55:26,260
[Jennie: Since I'm 30, No. 30.]

1780
00:55:25,610 --> 00:55:26,540
30.

1781
00:55:26,680 --> 00:55:27,900
I need one more number.

1782
00:55:26,820 --> 00:55:31,140
[To Gijun: 4, 9, 13, 17, 30, X]
[We'll leave the last number to your imagination]

1783
00:55:31,820 --> 00:55:33,420
[Sooji, I have another problem.]

1784
00:55:32,510 --> 00:55:33,560
What is it?

1785
00:55:33,690 --> 00:55:38,380
["I hope my vice principal
stays in my school next year.]

1786
00:55:38,380 --> 00:55:40,000
[Because thanks to my vice principal,]

1787
00:55:40,000 --> 00:55:45,340
we got to play badminton during lunch
and join tournaments, which I enjoyed."]

1788
00:55:43,970 --> 00:55:45,270
Vice principal...

1789
00:55:45,660 --> 00:55:49,020
[Write the number of the Ministry of Education.]

1790
00:55:49,500 --> 00:55:51,640
[You guys are really of no help at all.]

1791
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:53,780
[Hahaha.]
[Hahaha.]

1792
00:55:53,980 --> 00:55:56,300
[We're useless.]

1793
00:55:56,450 --> 00:55:57,810
Sooji.

1794
00:55:58,180 --> 00:56:02,820
["I hope I can have one free day.]

1795
00:56:00,370 --> 00:56:01,720
The reason is I can't enjoy school

1796
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:03,050
when all we do is study."

1797
00:56:03,620 --> 00:56:05,780
[Cataleya <3]
[Create a day when I can enjoy school!]

1798
00:56:06,660 --> 00:56:09,710
[I hope today is the day.]

1799
00:56:09,720 --> 00:56:11,420
Jeez, look at you.

1800
00:56:16,420 --> 00:56:20,740
[That's so cool.]

1801
00:56:19,560 --> 00:56:20,680
Really.

1802
00:56:21,240 --> 00:56:23,050
-Very cool. -Really.

1803
00:56:21,300 --> 00:56:22,820
[Agrees]

1804
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:24,880
I hope today is the day.

1805
00:56:27,900 --> 00:56:43,180
[I hope today is a happy day for you.]

1806
00:56:43,660 --> 00:56:47,020
[Sunghoon starts packing the snacks]

1807
00:56:47,660 --> 00:56:51,700
[Focusing silently]

1808
00:56:52,700 --> 00:56:55,740
[Cuts the beautiful ribbon carefully]

1809
00:56:56,340 --> 00:56:59,740
[Spreads open the wrapping paper carefully]

1810
00:57:00,900 --> 00:57:04,860
[Puts the snacks he bought inside]

1811
00:57:04,860 --> 00:57:09,540
[Killing it?]

1812
00:57:10,300 --> 00:57:13,220
[Scrunches up the wrapping paper
with his rough hands]

1813
00:57:13,820 --> 00:57:16,940
[Tightly]

1814
00:57:17,340 --> 00:57:20,700
[Wraps a beautiful red ribbon around it]

1815
00:57:22,500 --> 00:57:26,180
[Strangling it]

1816
00:57:26,420 --> 00:57:27,900
[Hmm...]

1817
00:57:28,460 --> 00:57:32,380
[Tightens it until he's satisfied]

1818
00:57:33,140 --> 00:57:36,300
[Just like that,
the fortune pouch with a topknot is completed]

1819
00:57:37,140 --> 00:57:39,980
[Don't misunderstand:
He's not crushing it but packaging it]

1820
00:57:40,660 --> 00:57:45,140
[Knots that are too tight
for the 2nd graders to untie]

1821
00:57:48,540 --> 00:57:51,620
[Gosh, I'm exhausted.]

1822
00:57:52,980 --> 00:57:55,500
[Physically drained]

1823
00:57:56,060 --> 00:57:58,300
[After we deliver the gifts...]

1824
00:57:58,300 --> 00:58:00,100
[Choo Sunghoon: I hope the kids watch the show.]

1825
00:58:00,100 --> 00:58:01,820
Right, yes.

1826
00:58:02,020 --> 00:58:03,290
-See how we prepared the gifts. -Yes.

1827
00:58:03,290 --> 00:58:05,040
Seeing our preparation process,

1828
00:58:05,040 --> 00:58:08,410
-they'd feel our sincerity more personally. -Yes.

1829
00:58:12,620 --> 00:58:15,860
[The uncle returns to packaging]

1830
00:58:16,340 --> 00:58:20,260
[Does the splits again to prevent back pain]

1831
00:58:21,700 --> 00:58:24,820
[His binding techniques back at work]

1832
00:58:26,690 --> 00:58:28,580
-Hongchul. -Yes.

1833
00:58:28,580 --> 00:58:30,220
[Don't you think it's fun?]

1834
00:58:30,140 --> 00:58:32,820
-I was excited when picking gifts. -Fun, right?

1835
00:58:33,140 --> 00:58:36,540
[I'm having fun too.]

1836
00:58:36,490 --> 00:58:38,930
Rather than giving gifts, wait, no.

1837
00:58:38,930 --> 00:58:43,140
[Rather than receiving gifts,
I prefer giving gifts.]

1838
00:58:40,700 --> 00:58:41,810
-Really. -Right?

1839
00:58:41,940 --> 00:58:43,600
I totally know how that feels.

1840
00:58:44,380 --> 00:58:49,860
[The snack pouches are wrapped imperfectly,
but they're filled with the joy of giving]

1841
00:58:51,900 --> 00:58:53,900
[Noh Hongchul: Dex, did you
write letters for everyone too?]

1842
00:58:54,220 --> 00:58:55,380
[No, just simply.]

1843
00:58:55,380 --> 00:58:58,570
-Just a note? -Yeah, just their names.

1844
00:58:58,700 --> 00:58:59,700
Really?

1845
00:59:00,420 --> 00:59:03,300
[Dex just wrote their names]

1846
00:59:03,980 --> 00:59:07,300
[Names?]

1847
00:59:08,020 --> 00:59:13,300
[Each gift tailored to their preferences,
everyone gets a different note]

1848
00:59:15,300 --> 00:59:19,740
[Manito Club members are
putting their heart and soul into the gifts]

1849
00:59:21,340 --> 00:59:24,100
[I'm so excited. Can't wait for tomorrow to come.]

1850
00:59:27,060 --> 00:59:29,140
[Wow, you really bought a lot.]

1851
00:59:29,460 --> 00:59:31,300
[Noh Hongchul: One's a sample.]

1852
00:59:31,300 --> 00:59:33,100
[Noh Hongchul: Since we bought the same (snacks).]

1853
00:59:33,270 --> 00:59:34,880
I wonder what the kids like.

1854
00:59:33,620 --> 00:59:37,100
[Brief snack time
to take a trip down memory lane]

1855
00:59:36,670 --> 00:59:38,260
Have you tried this before?

1856
00:59:37,980 --> 00:59:39,860
[Fried corn snack]

1857
00:59:38,560 --> 00:59:41,140
Corn? I've never seen it before.

1858
00:59:40,300 --> 00:59:44,220
[Sunghoon's first time seeing this snack]

1859
00:59:41,280 --> 00:59:42,560
-It's corn. -Yeah.

1860
00:59:42,810 --> 00:59:45,600
-Fried corn, so it's hard. -Oh, hard.

1861
00:59:46,100 --> 00:59:49,420
[Salivating]

1862
00:59:49,860 --> 00:59:51,140
[Do you have snacks left?]

1863
00:59:51,130 --> 00:59:52,170
This one.

1864
00:59:52,420 --> 00:59:55,540
[Sooji, do you want to try it?]

1865
00:59:54,410 --> 00:59:56,290
See if it's too hard for the kids to chew.

1866
00:59:56,180 --> 00:59:59,300
[Gets up happily]

1867
00:59:57,130 --> 00:59:59,130
-You just said... -One of them is...

1868
00:59:59,590 --> 01:00:00,400
Because they are 1st graders.

1869
00:59:59,820 --> 01:00:02,540
[Taste-test request for the kids]

1870
01:00:00,650 --> 01:00:02,170
Yes, 1st graders.

1871
01:00:02,980 --> 01:00:05,500
[Pours it into her mouth immediately]

1872
01:00:05,510 --> 01:00:06,380
They can't take this.

1873
01:00:06,300 --> 01:00:08,820
[(Too delicious that) I have to finish it all]

1874
01:00:07,350 --> 01:00:08,820
-Really? -Yes.

1875
01:00:09,220 --> 01:00:12,000
[Sunghoon's first time
trying the fried corn snack]

1876
01:00:11,900 --> 01:00:14,090
-It melts in your mouth. -Oh, it's good.

1877
01:00:12,000 --> 01:00:14,860
[Jennie's first time too]

1878
01:00:14,910 --> 01:00:16,010
-Is this your first time? -Yeah.

1879
01:00:15,940 --> 01:00:19,900
[K-snack that's only available in Korea]

1880
01:00:16,290 --> 01:00:17,810
-Really? -Yes.

1881
01:00:21,900 --> 01:00:25,820
[Mmm! It's good!]

1882
01:00:22,220 --> 01:00:24,250
-It melts in your mouth. -Oh, it's good.

1883
01:00:24,250 --> 01:00:25,310
Is it OK, Sunghoon?

1884
01:00:26,340 --> 01:00:30,100
[Hongchul takes out another snack]

1885
01:00:27,050 --> 01:00:28,620
What... I've never seen this before.

1886
01:00:28,620 --> 01:00:29,680
What? What's that?

1887
01:00:29,830 --> 01:00:31,310
This looks like tape, right?

1888
01:00:30,340 --> 01:00:33,460
[Candy that looks like tape]

1889
01:00:34,340 --> 01:00:37,460
[Don't eat plastic!]

1890
01:00:35,370 --> 01:00:36,610
This is...

1891
01:00:37,460 --> 01:00:38,530
[You eat the tape.]

1892
01:00:38,530 --> 01:00:43,300
[Culture shock for the uncle]

1893
01:00:38,530 --> 01:00:40,240
Eat the tape?

1894
01:00:40,420 --> 01:00:41,960
That's tape. It melts.

1895
01:00:42,100 --> 01:00:43,360
It melts in your mouth.

1896
01:00:43,700 --> 01:00:44,830
It's the kick.

1897
01:00:45,380 --> 01:00:48,340
[It's edible... Wow, it's melting!]

1898
01:00:46,980 --> 01:00:48,350
It melts, right?

1899
01:00:48,610 --> 01:00:51,130
-This is edible. -It's a little sweet!

1900
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:53,520
Sunghoon, it's to your taste?

1901
01:00:52,380 --> 01:00:55,500
[Also Jennie's first time trying the tape]

1902
01:00:53,640 --> 01:00:54,900
Yeah, give me the tape.

1903
01:00:55,050 --> 01:00:57,940
Keep biting it. I'll pull it.

1904
01:00:56,260 --> 01:01:00,340
[He accepts more tape, which is to his liking]

1905
01:00:58,190 --> 01:00:59,400
Really?

1906
01:00:59,980 --> 01:01:00,800
Of course.

1907
01:01:01,650 --> 01:01:02,750
Really,

1908
01:01:04,220 --> 01:01:08,260
[Sunghoon, have mine too]

1909
01:01:08,340 --> 01:01:10,520
It tastes like seaweed if you chew it.

1910
01:01:09,060 --> 01:01:12,420
[He doesn't refuse his little bro's kindness]

1911
01:01:13,580 --> 01:01:15,100
[Hahaha...]

1912
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:17,300
[Hahaha...]

1913
01:01:21,020 --> 01:01:23,340
[Hey!]

1914
01:01:24,060 --> 01:01:26,620
[Got caught!]

1915
01:01:27,500 --> 01:01:29,380
[Hey!]

1916
01:01:29,740 --> 01:01:32,700
[Dex watching Sunghoon,
who's taken a liking to the tape candy]

1917
01:01:33,260 --> 01:01:37,580
[Prepares the real tape secretly]

1918
01:01:38,020 --> 01:01:41,500
[Conveys it calmly]

1919
01:01:43,060 --> 01:01:45,900
[No wonder! No wonder it smelled weird!]

1920
01:01:46,190 --> 01:01:48,230
Sticks right to your mouth, right?

1921
01:01:46,420 --> 01:01:51,500
[And he was wondering
why it stuck right to his mouth]

1922
01:01:49,370 --> 01:01:51,810
You ate it without any doubt.

1923
01:01:54,700 --> 01:01:58,860
[Jennie: Part of my gift is about the classroom,
and I have to go decorate.]

1924
01:01:59,340 --> 01:02:04,780
[Jennie heads to the 5th graders' classroom]

1925
01:01:59,950 --> 01:02:01,460
-I'll be back. -Go ahead.

1926
01:02:01,560 --> 01:02:03,700
I'll go help you if I finish mine early.

1927
01:02:03,810 --> 01:02:05,140
Thank you.

1928
01:02:05,390 --> 01:02:06,190
Well, try this

1929
01:02:06,310 --> 01:02:07,610
coated-sphere snack, kkoedori.

1930
01:02:06,860 --> 01:02:12,380
[Another snack taste test request
before she leaves]

1931
01:02:07,610 --> 01:02:09,750
See if it tastes the same as our time.

1932
01:02:09,970 --> 01:02:11,340
See if it's deserving

1933
01:02:11,500 --> 01:02:12,770
of the name or not.

1934
01:02:12,620 --> 01:02:16,140
[Please compare the taste
from the past and the present]

1935
01:02:13,770 --> 01:02:14,420
Kkoedori.

1936
01:02:14,570 --> 01:02:15,910
Are you two done?

1937
01:02:16,080 --> 01:02:17,410
I'm almost done too.

1938
01:02:16,820 --> 01:02:20,100
[Analyzes while tasting it]

1939
01:02:18,320 --> 01:02:19,400
Guys.

1940
01:02:20,700 --> 01:02:24,540
[Lee Sooji: The kkoedori we had when we were young
were harder than we thought.]

1941
01:02:24,540 --> 01:02:26,140
[Lee Sooji: Back then, it was more...]

1942
01:02:27,340 --> 01:02:29,980
[Lee Sooji: More crispy, like rusk.]

1943
01:02:30,220 --> 01:02:31,540
[Rusk, haha.]

1944
01:02:33,380 --> 01:02:35,700
[Lee Sooji: What color is (the one I'm eating)?]

1945
01:02:34,560 --> 01:02:35,590
That's...

1946
01:02:36,240 --> 01:02:38,480
It has two colors, light and dark, right?

1947
01:02:38,480 --> 01:02:41,100
[Can you distinguish the taste?]

1948
01:02:38,610 --> 01:02:40,060
Can you tell them apart, Madam?

1949
01:02:40,060 --> 01:02:41,170
Let me try.

1950
01:02:41,410 --> 01:02:43,820
-Wait, let me taste each one first.
-Go ahead.

1951
01:02:41,900 --> 01:02:45,620
[(Light color) Pre-test inspection time]

1952
01:02:45,740 --> 01:02:48,070
Amazing. It clearly tastes like chocolate.

1953
01:02:45,940 --> 01:02:47,740
[Phew]

1954
01:02:48,180 --> 01:02:51,340
[Now tasting the dark one]

1955
01:02:48,420 --> 01:02:50,240
There's basically 0.0 chocolate inside,

1956
01:02:50,240 --> 01:02:51,120
so almost…

1957
01:02:51,260 --> 01:02:52,290
I'm starting.

1958
01:02:52,700 --> 01:02:55,820
[Boldly taking on the challenge]

1959
01:02:54,710 --> 01:02:55,890
Then I…

1960
01:02:56,420 --> 01:02:59,860
[First rinse mouth; Resetting the tongue]

1961
01:02:57,410 --> 01:02:58,500
This…

1962
01:03:00,690 --> 01:03:02,290
What is this?

1963
01:03:01,060 --> 01:03:03,340
[Open wide]

1964
01:03:03,800 --> 01:03:05,620
-If you guess right, that's really…
-Impressive.

1965
01:03:04,540 --> 01:03:09,460
[Ultimate taste-analyst showdown]

1966
01:03:05,730 --> 01:03:07,350
That would be seriously impressive.

1967
01:03:07,350 --> 01:03:10,350
Please don't open your eyes.
One, two, three… slowly.

1968
01:03:12,020 --> 01:03:18,820
[Focus only on the tip of the tongue]

1969
01:03:19,700 --> 01:03:21,100
I'm getting more nervous.

1970
01:03:20,100 --> 01:03:22,260
